        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:25PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paris, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Springville, Big Sandy, Haigler Ridge, Sunnyside, Manleyville,
Porter Court, Old Springville, India, and Big Sandy Unit Tennessee
National Wildlife Refuge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
